Patrick Willingham, executive 
director of The  Public Theater , discusses an ambitious 
Shakespeare in the Park season with a new Public Forum speakers 
series on money and its value in society. A musical production 
of Love's Labour's Lost continues at the Delacorte through 
August 18. He also describes the Public's 2013-2014 schedule 
which includes a collaboration with the Royal Shakespeare 
Company and a series of benefit concerts by Sting. Willingham 
talks with Bloomberg's  Kathleen Hays  and Vonnie Quinn on 
Bloomberg Radio's "The Hays Advantage."    (Source: Bloomberg)  Running time 17:56
 